area around a manhole cover.
6) Contracts, bids or proposals for any work at the intersection which involved repaving the
street(s) or any work which would impact the manhole covers. {Randolph & Wells, 1/1/2018 to present}

Please provide documentation beginning with year 2000 to the present for:
1.  Copies of any open inspections or violations and the results of such inspections and findings and/or orders.
2.  Any and all service requests for water/sewer work, historical records, etc. {1100 W Grand}

I would like to make a FOIA request for the years 2017 and 2018 for the Corwith Yard, located at 4012 South Kedzie Avenue, Chicago Illinois 60632, for any/all reports, documents, records, etc. pertaining to the following:
Plumbing inspection reports;
Sewer inspection reports;
Service requests for water and sewer work;
Water and sewer main inspection reports;
Water and sewer project and construction reports.

When we bought the property in April of 2019 we were told that the previous owners had broken water pipes due to freezing and that they replaced them, including the service line in from the city.  I would like to know if this service was performed and therefore if the old lead pipes were replaced during that time.  I would also like to know the size of pipe used to bring that new line into the property from the city and where it enters into the property (the front of the property or along the east side of the building toward the back of the building.
Thank you! 
P.S.  They didn't specify which year it occurred so if it doesn't show up in that date range and you can go back a couple of years, that would be helpful.  I appreciate it! {1724 W Rascher Ave}
